article.headline: Lehigh 63, Army 60
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Joe Knight scored 28 points as Lehigh held off Army 63-60 on Saturday night. Lehigh led 56-46 with 1:32 left but the Black Knights were able to cut the lead to five points with 26 seconds left on a 3-pointer by Dan Borcherdt. The Mountain Hawks shot 7-for-12 from the foul line in the final minute -- just good enough to hold off the Black Knights. Knight's big performance -- 13-for-18 from the foul line and 3-for-4 on 3-pointers -- carried the Mountain Hawks (10-8, 3-0 Patriot League) as the rest of the team shot just 27 percent from the floor. Jose Olivero (14 points) was the only other player in double figures for Lehigh. Jarell Brown led Army (4-11, 0-3) with 14 points and Matt Bell added 13. Corban Bates chipped in 11 points and 10 rebounds. Lehigh held a 23-18 lead at halftime and built a 14-point lead in the second half before Army rallied.
